guide.abstract: Most served Gentoo documents and translations

chapter.title: Most served Gentoo documents and translations

body.p: Quite a few translators and some authors have expressed a need for some stats about which documents are most read and whether translations are actually read. The following table shows the number of hits per document per language. No attempt has been made to filter out accesses by spiders, robots or any other non-human life form. Only successful GETs on documents under /proj, /doc and /news have been considered.

The following table might be updated with statistics from other days and/or weeks sporadically and randomly. Requests for updated data will not be answered and generating more hits on some documents and/or languages will only bring the wrath of infra down on you.
body.note: Documents like handbooks or an index.xml that uses metadoc get more hits because all parts or categories generate hits on the same file.

body.p: The following hits have been counted during 21 days between March 6, 2005 and March 26, 2005.
